02:19.570 --> 02:21.252
I used to shy away from that word.

02:21.272 --> 02:26.578
I don't know if you remember, but in the 80s and early 90s, that was a buzzword.

02:27.394 --> 02:32.399
And it had all sorts of different meanings, especially in the circles I was running in.

02:32.900 --> 02:36.504
And at that time, when they would talk about it, it sounded to me more like an occult.

02:37.705 --> 02:42.851
We're all going to live together in this community and do these things and the world can just pass us by.

02:42.911 --> 02:48.597
You might remember, like Jonestown, they were in community together.

02:49.037 --> 02:51.800
And so that gave bad community vibes to me.

02:52.961 --> 02:57.266
But everybody around me was using this word and

02:57.698 --> 03:07.090
Instead of it being harmonious togetherness for the cause of God, it was more like our own causes and I didn't like it.

03:09.112 --> 03:22.249
As a matter of fact, I think one of the reasons is I was an introvert back then, and it's surprising to me that I even began to like the idea, but once I understood it, I began to embrace it.

03:25.153 --> 03:26.194
The truth is,

03:26.434 --> 03:34.763
We all live in community of some sort if we're not isolated and living without anyone around.

03:36.644 --> 03:42.531
So when we look at community today, we're going to start with a regular community of people in a city.

03:43.772 --> 03:46.575
You know, your neighborhood is a local community, right?

03:47.295 --> 03:51.240
So those are the folks within a half mile or so, maybe a mile.

03:52.020 --> 03:53.682
That's your local community.

03:54.338 --> 04:00.005
Now that's not what we mean by communal living, that's different.

04:00.025 --> 04:04.430
But in every community, there are two types of residents.

04:05.752 --> 04:10.919
There are those who live in a place and there are those who live for it.

04:12.340 --> 04:13.141
There is a difference.

04:13.782 --> 04:21.371
The one who lives in a place first builds fences and the one who lives for a place plants gardens.

04:22.693 --> 04:23.474
In other words,

04:24.578 --> 04:26.099
How do I say this the best way?

04:26.139 --> 04:35.248
If you're going to plant an oak tree from seed or a sapling and you intend to plant it to be a shade tree, you're not planning on leaving it in a couple years.

04:36.910 --> 04:38.691
You plan to be there long term.

04:39.632 --> 04:48.000
So you know the difference between someone who wants to be there and be a part of it versus someone who's just transitioning.

04:48.841 --> 04:51.023
And those are the ones who don't put down roots.

04:51.123 --> 04:52.324
Those are transitioning.

04:52.805 --> 04:54.066
But those who are

04:55.170 --> 05:01.097
looking to make a home in that community, they make long-term plans.

05:01.197 --> 05:03.680
It's kind of like the difference between renting and owning.

05:05.582 --> 05:09.567
Rent, you're not too sure you care about the property, but in owning, you do.

05:09.607 --> 05:14.773
And in rent, you want it upkept, but you want someone else to do it.

05:15.554 --> 05:18.717
When you own it, if you don't upkeep it, it's going to fall apart.

05:21.901 --> 05:22.802
Some of us

05:23.042 --> 05:26.586
build walls to live our life in isolation.

05:28.368 --> 05:36.197
And when we do that, we never make a difference or have an impact on the lives around us.

05:39.741 --> 05:47.790
When God positions His people in a city or a community, it's never random.

05:48.711 --> 05:51.794
God is very intentional about what He does.

05:53.122 --> 06:04.774
I've tried to tell myself several times, well, this wasn't orchestrated by God, but I can't think of anything that God did not allow to happen and orchestrate when you look at the big picture.

06:08.058 --> 06:17.048
We are rooted in God's presence, and we are sent along roots or routes of purpose.

06:17.728 --> 06:22.994
So we dig deep by coming to church and learning and putting our

06:23.458 --> 06:32.230
roots down into deep wells of salvation, but it's so we can go out and serve on the routes the highways and the byways around us.

06:35.014 --> 06:42.245
In other words, we're not just occupying a church, we're ambassadors for the kingdom of God because of it.

06:44.908 --> 06:51.698
Our address, zip code, if you will, is a part of the assignment God gives each of us.

06:55.682 --> 06:57.825
Now, let me say it this way.

06:58.846 --> 07:07.798
He sends us out and he asks us to do things, but God is the one who causes the increase.

07:07.818 --> 07:11.523
We may do the labor, but we partner with God.

07:12.624 --> 07:13.646
We don't do this alone.

07:14.227 --> 07:16.389
If God asks us to do something, he's going to help us.

07:18.572 --> 07:22.898
In Jeremiah chapter 29 verses 4 through 7, I read verse 7,

07:23.874 --> 07:29.743
The story is that Israelites were exiles in Babylon, the Babylonian captivity.

07:30.063 --> 07:42.922
And yet God said to them in that section, build houses, plant gardens and multiply there in captivity.

07:45.265 --> 07:51.474
So wherever God plants us, wherever we are planted, God expects fruit.

07:53.570 --> 07:58.901
Doesn't matter what your circumstances are, God can use you to bless another.

08:00.625 --> 08:02.829
And sometimes you go, well, I don't have much resources.

08:03.350 --> 08:06.076
God does not need resources.

08:06.116 --> 08:11.026
He needs willing people to share the good news, which is free.

