wherever you are planted, even if you are in transition, you can still share the gospel of Jesus Christ.

09:44.977 --> 09:57.874
God roots us and he roots us in his presence, not by his preference, because being rooted doesn't mean you're stuck

09:57.954 --> 10:27.954
in some place some people don't like to be tied down you know what i mean but it means being steady where you are consistency is important people need to know that if we're doing the food pantry on a third Wednesday that we can do it on a third Wednesday and now it's a second Wednesday this month sorry for god to tell you or no we're going to do it on the fourth one next month we'll go back to the third and maybe we'll do it on the first you just never know

10:28.162 --> 10:29.905
They can't rely on that.

10:30.506 --> 10:43.726
So that consistency, that steadfastness to be faithful and people that understand that we will do what we say will do when we do it is a part of a witness of faithfulness to God.

10:48.494 --> 10:52.199
We don't stay in one place because we're comfortable.

10:52.760 --> 10:56.466
We stay there because God actually called us to be where we are.

10:59.586 --> 11:09.296
Psalm chapter 1 verse 3 says, he shall be like a tree planted by the rivers of water that brings forth its fruit in its season.

11:10.878 --> 11:16.124
That's the one who nurtures themselves on God's word and cherishes it.

11:16.824 --> 11:21.469
And that word causes us to draw deep from the truths of God.

11:24.052 --> 11:29.458
So when we're rooted in God's presence, we can produce fruit

11:29.538 --> 11:30.840
in any climate.

11:34.845 --> 11:36.287
When I was a kid, I moved a lot.

11:38.470 --> 11:38.970
A lot.

11:39.911 --> 11:51.907
I think one day I was in my mid to late 30s, maybe 40s, and I was counting all the times I had moved, and it was once for every year of my life I had moved.

11:52.668 --> 11:57.234
Didn't mean I was moving every year, and then some years I moved three or four times.

11:58.434 --> 12:05.623
And well, as a college student in a tenorant pastor or a son of an independent tenorant pastor, you're going to move a lot.

12:06.264 --> 12:06.844
And we did.

12:06.884 --> 12:07.946
And so did I.

12:07.966 --> 12:13.733
And so whenever I grew up, people would ask, what's your hometown?

12:15.875 --> 12:17.758
I didn't have one in particular.

12:18.178 --> 12:21.883
I had one in general that I referred to where we spent six years.

12:23.605 --> 12:27.730
And I had a place I called the home place where my parents owned a retirement.

12:27.938 --> 12:34.646
cabin that they retired to in the 80s, 1980s, not their 80s.

12:35.527 --> 12:45.658
And they, so I would call that the home place, but that place we live for six years in my grade school years, I call that the hometown.

12:47.481 --> 12:51.565
But as I've gotten older, I now say my hometown is Paducah.

12:53.347 --> 12:55.730
Lo-no, if you will.

12:57.378 --> 12:59.501
Because I put down roots.

13:02.485 --> 13:06.891
And I've lived there longer than anywhere else I've ever lived.

13:06.911 --> 13:08.833
And so I kind of like that.

13:08.873 --> 13:10.716
I like consistency.

13:10.756 --> 13:15.462
I like that you have the ability to know you're going to be there tomorrow as well.

13:15.963 --> 13:22.271
One of the most difficult things to face in life is when you're not sure where you're going to stay or your next meal is coming from.

13:22.792 --> 13:27.218
But once you know that, you can start to grow and produce and be

13:27.330 --> 13:29.413
impactful in the world around you.

13:34.682 --> 13:43.315
So when we're rooted by God in a place where we call home, that's where God's asking us to bear fruit.

13:46.981 --> 13:51.488
Now it doesn't mean you don't do mission work or reach out like that.

13:51.969 --> 13:55.474
It means that your primary place

13:55.874 --> 14:01.801
of mission in ministry is around your home or within a few miles of your church.

14:02.902 --> 14:06.586
Because that's where the church community is working.

14:12.593 --> 14:19.360
And when we begin to look at our community around us, we need to look at it through God's eyes, not our own.

14:21.603 --> 14:24.466
John chapter 5 verse 17 says,

14:25.250 --> 14:26.351
This is Jesus speaking.

14:26.571 --> 14:31.717
My father has been working until now, and I have been working.

14:32.698 --> 14:35.962
Which means that God is at work all around us.

14:36.983 --> 14:44.050
And if you just ask Him to show you, you can join Him in what He's trying to do and be a part of what God's already doing.

14:45.812 --> 14:54.642
I think it was Henry Black being an experiencing God that said, if you want to be a part of what God's doing, don't try something new.

14:54.850 --> 14:56.852
Figure out what he's already doing and join him in that.

14:58.575 --> 15:01.098
And sometimes that's easier said than done.

15:01.138 --> 15:03.941
Sometimes God's asking you to do a new thing.

15:04.322 --> 15:12.612
But either way Jesus didn't bring God into his city when he came.

15:12.672 --> 15:17.999
He showed them or revealed God's activity that was already there.

15:22.284 --> 15:23.986
I like to think of it like this.

15:24.706 --> 15:31.935
We had blind Bartimaeus, we had Zacchaeus, all these different folks in different communities.

15:32.977 --> 15:37.302
And nobody was showing Zacchaeus how to live a righteous life.

15:38.303 --> 15:44.171
And nobody was willing to let blind Bartimaeus, if you remember his story, they told him to help himself.

15:44.391 --> 15:45.352
They weren't going to help him.

15:46.474 --> 15:48.216
And the opportunity was right in front of him.

15:50.038 --> 15:52.882
Or the man who was born lame.

15:54.274 --> 16:09.132
and Peter and John came to the temple and helped them to walk again and they started praising God in the temple making a ruckus at a time of prayer and they were mad because he was disturbing their prayer time.

16:12.256 --> 16:15.640
God is doing a miracle and they're going, do it somewhere else.

16:16.922 --> 16:19.445
Don't bug us with God's miracle.

16:19.465 --> 16:20.306
But guess what?

16:21.986 --> 16:24.649
God is always working if we're willing to look for it.

16:25.130 --> 16:31.277
If we're willing to not close our mind of what's possible and see the expectation of what God's trying to do.

16:31.297 --> 16:35.682
At that point needs can become opportunities.

16:37.084 --> 16:44.232
Strangers can become partners with us and change becomes an invitation.

16:47.576 --> 16:49.298
But we can get bogged down.

16:49.570 --> 17:04.686
If you know what I mean by bogged down just like we're spinning our wheels, not going anywhere, and how we're used to seeing things and the expectations that we have for them.

17:04.706 --> 17:12.595
There's a young man who was at a church I was pastoring, and the people had given up on him pretty much.

17:12.935 --> 17:15.698
He was still coming, but they'd given up on him.

17:16.258 --> 17:18.982
Other pastors said, I've tried this kid's hopeless.

17:19.322 --> 17:20.965
We can't do anything with it.

17:20.985 --> 17:21.946
We tried everything.

17:22.507 --> 17:28.936
And I said, I think God's bigger than your willingness to give up.

17:30.959 --> 17:32.462
I don't think God's done with this kid.

17:33.643 --> 17:41.154
And so I befriended him and began to walk alongside him and share the gospel, especially by love.

17:42.076 --> 17:43.698
And gradually, he warmed up.

17:45.090 --> 17:49.977
And it began to see how things were in the church and how to love.

17:50.078 --> 18:03.538
It was interesting because he had never been in church, so he didn't know that the language in church shouldn't be like the ones he hangs around when he was with his friends.

18:05.681 --> 18:11.410
And so it was like, oh, I can't believe you said that word in church.

18:11.810 --> 18:14.955
But he said it and it's like you don't say that.

18:15.275 --> 18:16.958
I won't say that outside of church.

18:16.978 --> 18:17.979
But he said it right there.

18:17.999 --> 18:21.024
He was happy when he said it.

18:21.044 --> 18:21.705
He wasn't mad.

18:21.745 --> 18:23.808
He was just using it like God is good.

18:23.868 --> 18:25.551
And this is a part of it.

18:26.011 --> 18:28.295
And I'm celebrating in the only way I know how.

18:28.736 --> 18:34.464
And other people look defended, but I look like that's a new way to praise God.

18:34.885 --> 18:40.914
And so later I called him aside and I said, you know,

18:41.442 --> 18:48.353
I don't know if you know this or not, but there are certain words we don't want to use in church because we're trying to be more reverent and change the language we use.

18:48.693 --> 18:55.604
Because when God gets a hold of us, He changes everything about us, including how we represent ourselves and our language.

18:57.427 --> 18:58.008
And you know what?

18:59.109 --> 18:59.891
He said, thank you.

19:01.453 --> 19:02.875
Thank you for teaching me that.

19:03.416 --> 19:05.039
I'll not do that anymore.

19:05.640 --> 19:08.524
But everybody else was whispering like, oh, he said that word.

19:08.624 --> 19:09.746
And they wouldn't.

19:10.050 --> 19:15.699
Hell him or share with him because they'd give him up on him.

19:19.244 --> 19:23.551
There's someone inside of me said, don't give up.

19:23.571 --> 19:28.358
And he became, believe it or not, a stalwart in that church.

19:29.079 --> 19:30.081
Hands and everything.

19:30.762 --> 19:32.645
And the people said he was indispensable.

19:33.246 --> 19:38.674
And after a while, when he would tell his story, people'd say, I can't believe you ever that way.

19:38.914 --> 19:40.837
It's how much of a change you made.

19:43.821 --> 19:55.136
So if you get bogged down your expectations of how someone's supposed to be, you may never see how God's actually working on them right now and not joining in that process.

