This is priceless.

26:14.677 --> 26:15.698
And I'll tell you why.

26:15.970 --> 26:21.616
Because once somebody has a bad reputation, it's hard to get it back to be a good one, doesn't it?

26:21.636 --> 26:22.837
There's old so-and-so.

26:22.877 --> 26:28.302
Not there's who used to be old so-and-so, a new reading believer in Jesus Christ.

26:28.363 --> 26:29.484
They still talk about who they were.

26:31.225 --> 26:38.313
So having a bad reputation, you can't really repair, but having a good one is invaluable.

26:39.133 --> 26:43.698
I think anybody who's ever been in sales or made living dealing with people would say,

26:44.258 --> 26:48.484
that if you had credibility and trust, that makes all the difference in the world.

26:48.785 --> 26:51.569
Because if you don't have it, I don't want to talk to you.

26:54.794 --> 27:00.522
We have what I call gospel gold reputation.

27:00.542 --> 27:05.549
When you talk about New Liberty, United Methodist Church and the community, people aren't going, oh, you go there?

27:06.691 --> 27:07.713
Like, what's wrong with you?

27:07.853 --> 27:09.695
It's like, oh, I know that church.

27:10.256 --> 27:10.957
It does this.

27:11.498 --> 27:12.379
Oh, I know that church.

27:12.419 --> 27:14.162
Someone so goes there, used to go there.

27:14.466 --> 27:16.429
they have a good feeling about it.

27:17.430 --> 27:18.752
So you can harness that.

27:20.775 --> 27:21.657
The community does.

27:26.424 --> 27:41.266
So when we seek the peace of our community, when we seek, and I mean peace of heart and peace of mind, in Jeremiah 29 and seven, the verse I started with,

27:42.818 --> 27:45.582
It says, seek the peace and prosperity of the city.

27:45.622 --> 27:48.387
The word is shalom.

27:51.211 --> 27:52.293
It's all missing at the end.

27:53.274 --> 27:54.316
Christ be your shalom.

27:55.298 --> 27:56.840
This is what he uses.

27:57.341 --> 28:01.527
And that word means wholeness, harmony, rightness.

28:02.269 --> 28:07.477
We want the shalom of God to be on our community.

28:08.438 --> 28:10.802
That's what we say when we sing that.

28:12.226 --> 28:18.053
When the church pursues shalom for its community, this is what happens.

28:18.514 --> 28:25.823
It becomes a prophetic presence, not just preaching salvation, but also demonstrating it.

28:29.527 --> 28:35.835
It's like a lighthouse rooted in radiant, showing folks away home or away from the dangers.

28:37.897 --> 28:41.682
And by prophetic word, I want to share with you what I mean by that.

28:42.594 --> 28:50.005
Because prophetic words are more than like prophecy about what's coming, future stuff.

28:50.025 --> 28:54.612
In the scripture, most of the time a prophetic word was just expounding the word of God.

28:54.652 --> 28:55.273
What truth?

28:56.675 --> 28:59.720
Showing what God's saying in the scripture would wisdom.

29:01.242 --> 29:10.175
It's what God's trying to teach us and tell us more than about what you're supposed to expect in times type prophecy.

29:11.277 --> 29:12.018
Teaching

29:12.482 --> 29:15.005
encouraging and challenging.

29:15.506 --> 29:19.250
This is what true prophetic teaching is.

29:19.851 --> 29:24.376
It's not about what's coming, it's about what does God say to us.

29:24.957 --> 29:33.347
So when we look at these verses I'm sharing today, I'm trying to share with you what I believe God's telling us and that's a prophetic word.

29:35.309 --> 29:36.210
It doesn't mean

29:36.610 --> 29:39.014
You do this and that'll happen or that's going to happen.

29:39.034 --> 29:39.975
So you better do this.

29:40.076 --> 29:50.853
It's more this is how God is preparing us and showing us and this called the vining the word of God with truth and wisdom, which I pray is what we're doing.

29:50.913 --> 30:01.170
This message is one of those moments where God can meet you where you are and speak into your life.

30:03.778 --> 30:08.024
The Holy Spirit starts working and you feel something like, man, I needed to hear that.

30:08.405 --> 30:10.267
I'm going to do this because of that.

30:10.828 --> 30:18.239
Now you know it's a prophetic word because the word of God is living active and powerful and it cuts out the junk out of our lives.

30:19.020 --> 30:27.092
So when something is spoken from the pulpit or you read something in Scripture and all of a sudden you go, you know, God, I feel convicted about this.

30:27.152 --> 30:28.134
I need to make a change.

30:28.394 --> 30:28.855
Help me.

30:29.856 --> 30:31.218
That's a prophetic word.

30:36.642 --> 30:42.209
So how do we do this individually or collectively?

30:44.331 --> 30:51.580
Now, some of these things that I want to share with you, there's four, are very common sense.

30:52.521 --> 30:56.366
The first one is to pray for our community and the church's ministry in it.

30:57.187 --> 30:58.308
Everybody can do that.

30:59.309 --> 31:00.290
They have an impact.

31:00.331 --> 31:06.578
Ask God, help us to have an impact on people's lives who are here and who will be here.

31:06.946 --> 31:08.629
Show us how to be ready for that.

31:08.970 --> 31:10.032
That's a simple prayer.

31:11.855 --> 31:15.682
And then there are things that happen in the community, events and things like that.

31:16.143 --> 31:19.169
And sometimes we're not involved in them because it's not our thing.

31:19.670 --> 31:27.203
But if we get involved in them, then we can meet people who we can understand who they are and start to talk about them.

31:27.223 --> 31:30.770
So we learn the rhythm of the needs of the people in the community.

31:34.466 --> 31:39.532
so we can attend and listen to what the community is saying and what it needs.

31:40.574 --> 31:50.586
Whenever that might be, and if we're involved in those things, then people see us and trust us more because they know we care about our community.

31:57.315 --> 32:03.282
And then we can partner with existing efforts that align with kingdom values.

32:03.682 --> 32:08.509
There's already good stuff happening in our area that we can actually help with.

32:10.071 --> 32:12.454
You might say, well, but we want our church to do that.

32:12.935 --> 32:25.693
If we're doing it as a church intentionally and saying we're helping you, but from New Liberty and we want to help you, all of a sudden people say, hey, New Liberty's the kind of church that comes up and supports us in this.

32:25.713 --> 32:28.357
And then the next time they need something, who are they going to call?

32:28.377 --> 32:31.922
They're going to call New Liberty and say,

32:32.098 --> 32:34.282
You guys have been such an influence.

32:34.923 --> 32:36.305
Can you help us with this?

32:38.308 --> 32:45.981
And then when we say we have an idea about something we want to do, we help us.

32:46.923 --> 32:49.667
They're very willing to listen and they're very willing to help.

32:51.210 --> 32:56.218
The last thing we can do is celebrate stories of impact from our community in areas.

32:57.680 --> 32:58.642
It's very important

32:59.298 --> 33:02.621
What I mean by that, other churches out there are doing some good stuff.

33:03.602 --> 33:07.005
And we can partner with them if they're doing something we want to do.

33:07.926 --> 33:09.267
That God is leading us to do.

33:09.808 --> 33:15.753
Sometimes we learn from another church what they're doing to help us learn to do it here.

33:16.294 --> 33:18.716
Sometimes we go there and help them.

33:18.756 --> 33:24.822
And then we can ask them to partner with us.

33:27.204 --> 33:29.266
Not saying this is what we want to do, but

33:29.602 --> 33:32.505
For example, we're helping say a church with what they're doing.

33:32.545 --> 33:35.749
We say, you know, we want to expand our food pantry ministry.

33:35.809 --> 33:39.313
Maybe making a clothing pantry too, but we need a little more help.

33:39.633 --> 33:41.836
We want to do it more regularly than just once a month.

33:41.856 --> 33:48.403
And if you all would be willing to help with us and pick a week and provide the food for us for that week, then we could do it every week.

33:49.364 --> 33:50.586
Would you all be willing to help us?

33:50.626 --> 33:52.888
Because I don't think you have a food ministry, but we do.

33:53.749 --> 33:54.610
And we know how to do it.

33:54.851 --> 33:55.912
And we've got people who will come.

33:57.213 --> 33:57.874
Guess what?

33:58.466 --> 34:04.873
That's saying I'm invested in the community and all we're asking for is help to minister better.

34:04.913 --> 34:07.436
There's nothing wrong with that.

34:11.520 --> 34:15.204
We are only limited by our willingness to do what it takes.

34:18.648 --> 34:24.754
Remember, there's no such thing as someone who God doesn't want to redeem.

34:28.738 --> 34:30.640
And we reach them any way we can.

34:33.103 --> 34:37.528
So if they're in your path, trust that God put them for a reason.

34:39.089 --> 34:39.690
Can you do that?

34:40.851 --> 34:42.153
You trust that God will do that?

34:43.154 --> 34:51.523
Can you think like that this week, starting today, that they're in your path, God put them there?

34:53.225 --> 34:54.066
Let's find out why.

34:56.354 --> 35:07.531
If you're willing to do that, I'm going to ask as we go to Holy Communion that you say, God, help me see what you need me to see and the people you need me to reach and help me do that.

35:08.472 --> 35:20.110
To either resource to them or be the one to tell them so that I'm making an impact, whether for myself to do it or someone else, to make those connections.

35:22.634 --> 35:25.298
To me, simple enough,

35:25.666 --> 35:26.907
community is connections.

35:28.429 --> 35:29.851
And I'm going to give you a perfect example.

35:32.113 --> 35:36.938
My wife and I have been leading the Celebrate Recovery Ministry at Heartland since 2009.

35:36.978 --> 35:39.741
It's now Concord and I met this church.

35:39.761 --> 35:45.508
2009, most of our friendships have come through that ministry.

35:47.390 --> 35:55.058
So when I had a problem with the floor and I wanted to get it done, I first called my son, he said he'd come and he came.

35:55.970 --> 36:01.418
And I asked a guy from Celebrate, I said, Hey, I'm working on this floor.

36:01.438 --> 36:02.199
Do you have time to go?

36:02.960 --> 36:03.460
I'll be there.

36:04.262 --> 36:04.842
I'll be there.

36:05.543 --> 36:07.566
You see, community supports each other.

36:07.586 --> 36:08.387
They help each other.

36:08.447 --> 36:16.919
He knows if I need something, I'm going to be there because I have been in his life for a long time and I've helped him with a lot of situations.

36:17.280 --> 36:18.862
So he wanted to help me right back.

36:20.464 --> 36:21.906
And this is, this is the truth.

36:22.562 --> 36:26.086
Yesterday, around midnight, he leaves because we're not done yet.

36:26.106 --> 36:28.088
And he says, I'm going to come back tomorrow morning at 730.

36:28.108 --> 36:29.189
That's all right with you.

36:29.550 --> 36:31.432
And I'm going to work on it till church.

36:32.993 --> 36:34.155
And I said, you don't have to do that.

36:34.215 --> 36:34.916
And he says, no, no.

36:36.377 --> 36:37.518
You're a brother in need.

36:38.800 --> 36:39.400
I want to help.

36:40.001 --> 36:41.403
That's what community says.

36:42.043 --> 36:51.794
Right now, he's in my kitchen laying vinyl plank because he knows I can't get it done before my wife gets home.

36:52.482 --> 36:53.303
if it isn't done.

36:53.343 --> 37:10.859
Now, and I said, the overwhelming thankfulness and gratitude of someone willing to do something, I would have had to pay thousands of dollars to someone else to do it and he's doing it because he cares.

37:12.241 --> 37:13.302
That's community.

37:13.922 --> 37:17.125
When you communicate that, a lot of change.

37:18.727 --> 37:22.290
And they want to get back to you in a way that says thank you.

37:22.498 --> 37:26.283
or help you with what you're doing because it made an impact on them.

37:26.643 --> 37:27.324
Does that make sense?

37:30.768 --> 37:31.228
Pray with me.

37:33.531 --> 37:37.356
Lord, thank you for planting us right here.

37:39.819 --> 37:41.581
So help us to see the people around us.

37:44.585 --> 37:49.170
To see them as you see them, full of promise and potential,

37:50.338 --> 37:58.611
root us deeply in your presence and send us faithfully along the routes of purpose that you've called us to.

38:00.254 --> 38:03.079
Make our church a living testimony of your peace.

38:07.045 --> 38:12.594
And then as we prepare for Holy Communion, I invite you to

